<h1>AnchorsAway Help</h1>
<table>
	<tr><td><img src="aa1.JPG" border="1" width="200" height="150"></td>
			<td><ul>
				<li>Each round, you will be given a pool of letters to place to make words.</li>
				<li>In Level 1, there will be one word; in Level 2, two words, and so on.</li>
				<li>Words are 4, 5, and 6 letters.</li>
				<li>Four-letter words have 2 letters to be placed; the others have 3.</li>
				<li>When you have found all the pieces in the maze, the puzzle will light up for you to solve it.</li>
			</ul></td></tr>
	<tr><td><img src="aa2.JPG" border="1" width="200" height="150"></td>
			<td><ul>
				<li>When you click on a letter in the pool, it will highlight yellow.</li>
				<li>Once you have a letter highlighted, click on its destination to place it.</li>
				<li>If the letters you have placed form a valid word, its color will change to orange.</li>
				<li>Any valid word will be accepted; it does not need to be the one intended.</li>
			</ul></td></tr>
	<tr><td><img src="aa3.JPG" border="1" width="200" height="150"></td>
			<td><ul>
				<li>If you get stuck, click on the WORDS button for help.</li>
			</ul></td></tr>
	<tr><td><img src="aa4.JPG" border="1" width="200" height="200"></td>
			<td><ul>
				<li>The WORDS button will display a list of words that fit the pattern presented for each word.</li>
			</ul></td></tr>
	<tr><td><img src="aa5.JPG" border="1" width="200" height="150"></td>
			<td><ul>
				<li>When you have placed all the letters to form words, the puzzle will darken.</li>
				<li>The words used to create the puzzle will then be displayed at the top.</li>
			</ul></td></tr>
</table>
